This paper discusses the translation of a knowledge representation language into Java, which involves programming language concepts such as attribute grammars, nondeterministic functional language, and backtracking. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). However, the paper also discusses the practical application development of knowledge-based systems, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions experimental results, which could be related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
